%h1#privacy-policy PRIVACY POLICY
%p Our visitors privacy is extremely important to us.
%p
  In this document we specify the privacy guidelines that you must accept if you decide to visit and browse the site
  %a{:href => "http://www.joinple.com"} www.joinple.com
  (hereinafter called Website).
%p These privacy policies may be updated to align to law modifications, to adapt to any new technology or for other reasons, so we ask that you check it regularly.
%h2#personal-data Personal data
%p
  We inform you that your personal data (name, surname, email address, mailing address, etc.) that you provide voluntarily to the webmaster by filling in forms (registration site, newsletter subscription, participation in competitions, etc ...) or  sending e-mail, will be treated in accordance with the provisions set in the Italian
  %a{:href => "http://www.privacy.it/privacycode-en.html"} Legislative Decree. 196/2003
  Code regarding the protection of personal data.
%p Such data will be used exclusively for the purposes indicated in relation to the use of services.
%h2#aims-of-treatment Aims of treatment
%p The above personal data will be used exclusively in relation to:
%ul
  %li registration to Joinple®
  %li requests for information on Joinple® services and platform
  %li request for competitions participation
  %li subscription to the newsletter.
%p Except above specified, about navigation data, the user has the option to supply or not his personal data in the forms available on the website or by email.
%p The lack of data imply the inability to provide the services requested.
%h2#rights-of-concerned-people Rights of concerned people
%p
  The owners of the personal data have the right at any time to obtain confirmation of the existence of such data and to know the content and the origin, verify the accuracy or request the integration, the update, or the correction (art. 7 of the Italian Legislative Decree 196/2003). According to the same article the owner of the data has the right to request cancellation, transformation into anonymous form or block of data used against the law, and to take position in any case, for legal reasons, to their treatment.
  Requests should be sent by e-mail at:
  %a{:href => "mailto:info@joinple.it"} info@joinple.it
%h2#navigation-data Navigation Data
%p
  The computer systems and the software applications used to run the site acquires, during their normal operations, some personal data whose transmission is implicit in the Internet communication protocols. This information are not collected to be associated with any specific individual, but by their nature could, through processing and association with data held by third parties, be used in order to identify users.
  This category of data includes IP addresses or domain names of computers used by users connecting to the site, URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) of requested resources, time of request, the method used to submit the request to the server, the file size obtained in response, the numerical code indicating the status of response from the server (successful, error, etc.) and other parameters regarding the operating system and computer environment.
%p These data are used only to obtain anonymous statistical information on the Site, to improve the service and the performance and are deleted immediately after their processing.
%p The data could be used to ascertain responsibility in case of computer crimes against the site.
